<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="623" pageId="7" pageNumber="622" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[828,1438,1276,2081]" lastBlockId="8.[151,760,190,405]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="623" pageId="7" pageNumber="622">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[828,961,1674,1697]" pageId="7" pageNumber="622">Comments.</emphasis>
As 
<taxonomicName box="[1013,1108,1674,1697]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Pentatoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="622" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="halys">
<emphasis box="[1013,1108,1674,1697]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="622">H. halys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is fixed in this paper as the type species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1864" box="[995,1143,1706,1729]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Halyomorpha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="622" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[995,1143,1706,1729]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="622">Halyomorpha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, its identity is of particular interest. The species was described based on an unspecified number of specimens (
<typeStatus box="[1150,1246,1770,1793]" pageId="7" pageNumber="622">syntypes</typeStatus>
) from ‘China’; a subsequent paper (Sඍචඅ 1856) stated that the specimens were provided by ‘Dom. [= Mr.] Hamberg’. Two females from the same lot of specimens, matching the original description (Sඍචඅ 1855) and information subsequently provided by the same author (Sඍචඅ 1856) and certainly belonging to the type material of 
<taxonomicName box="[1191,1371,1962,1985]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Pentatoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="622" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="halys">
<emphasis box="[1191,1371,1962,1985]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="622">Pentatoma halys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, have been located in NHRS; to facilitate a revision of the genus, the one in better condition is illustrated here (
<figureCitation box="[1301,1425,2026,2049]" captionStart="Figs 24–26" captionStartId="10.[151,188,1516,1535]" captionTargetBox="[151,1416,189,1472]" captionTargetId="figure-13@10.[151,1436,189,1491]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 24–26. Pentatoma halys Stål, 1855, female syntype (NHRS): 24 – dorsal view, 25 – ventral view, 26 – labels. Scale bar in mm. Orig. D. Rédei." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5821313" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5821313/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="622">Figs 24–26</figureCitation>
). Both specimens are consistent with the identification of this species by recent authors (e.g., Jඈඌංൿඈඏ &amp; KൾඋඓΗඇൾඋ 1978 or Vඣඍൾκ et al. 2014).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,760,190,405]" lastBlockId="8.[828,1437,190,405]" pageId="8" pageNumber="623">
Two additional females, one from ‘Hongkong’ and one from ‘Japonia’ [= 
<collectingCountry box="[336,401,286,309]" name="Japan" pageId="8" pageNumber="623">Japan</collectingCountry>
], were labelled as types and pinned together with the above listed 
<specimenCount box="[460,597,318,341]" pageId="8" pageNumber="623" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">two syntypes</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[629,715,318,341]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Pentatoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="623" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="halys">
<emphasis box="[629,715,318,341]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="623">H. halys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but as they are not from the type locality of 
<taxonomicName box="[578,666,350,373]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Pentatoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="623" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="halys">
<emphasis box="[578,666,350,373]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="623">H. halys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as listed by Sඍචඅ (1855, 1856), they are considered as having no type status. One of them is provided with a handwritten label ‘ 
<taxonomicName authority="Voll" authorityName="Voll" box="[899,1215,222,245]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Pentatoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="623" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dalpadoides">
<emphasis box="[899,1156,222,245]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="623">Pentatoma dalpadoides</emphasis>
Voll
</taxonomicName>
[enhoven]’, which is apparently an unpublished name; 
<taxonomicName authority="Vollenhoven, 1867" authorityName="Vollenhoven" authorityYear="1867" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Gynenica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="623" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dalpadoides">
<emphasis box="[1195,1436,254,277]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="623">Gynenica dalpadoides</emphasis>
Vollenhoven, 1867
</taxonomicName>
(currently 
<taxonomicName box="[1163,1427,286,309]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Platynopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="623" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dalpadoides">
<emphasis box="[1163,1427,286,309]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="623">Platynopus dalpadoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) is an unrelated species belonging to 
<taxonomicName box="[1230,1331,318,341]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="623" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Asopinae">Asopinae</taxonomicName>
(TΗඈආൺඌ 1994), its type material is deposited in RMNH and has been seen by us (D. Rédei, pers. observ.).
</paragraph>
